      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 97: Adding `pluginData` directly to the serialized `SwarmMessage` DBus struct changes the wire signature and can break compatibility with older daemons/clients that still emit or expect the previous 8-field struct. This is especially risky because the codebase still supports finding libjami externally. Please either gate this with a protocol/API version check or keep the DBus struct backward-compatible by reading/writing optional plugin metadata through a compatible extension path.\n\n```suggestion\n// Keep the DBus SwarmMessage signature stable unless both sides are version-gated.\n// Add plugin data through a versioned signal/struct or a backward-compatible metadata map.\n```",
      "revId": "fa8277ee9bc89a7692ec2416b257b2ca8960291f",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
